wikipedia_page.main: Kate Ellen Louisa Cutler (14 August 1864 – 14 May 1955) was an English singer and actress, known in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries as an ingénue in musical comedies, and later as a character actress in comic and dramatic plays.  She is possibly best known for walking out of the lead role in Noël Coward's The Vortex in 1924 shortly before opening night.
